  "commentary": "With SPX at 6764.97 sitting below the GEX flip at 6784, dealers are currently in positive gamma territory and likely buying this dip as part of their hedging flow. The massive +14.2B gamma wall at 6780 creates a strong magnetic pull just above current levels, while the -9.8B negative gamma at 6750 provides a floor where dealers would aggressively buy any breakdown. The recent GEX surge combined with the PIN regime suggests dealers will continue to provide liquidity by fading moves, creating resistance into 6775-6780 and support at 6750.\n\nBottom line: expect price to gravitate toward the 6775-6780 zone with limited downside below 6750.",
